This is a simple script for search and install of packages.

Installation:
run the installscript - "sh install.sh"
edit the file "/etc/inst.conf" to fit your needs 
(you can use both ftp and http sites)
run "makelist_inst" (this is automated in v1.0 and newer)

SYNTAX:
sinst "package" - search for a package.
inst "package" - installs a package
inst -c "number" - installs a packages 
(the number is displayed by sinst befor the packagename).


A few examples:
'sinst bash' <- lists all bash packages (including different flavours).
147 bash-3.0-static.tgz
148 bash-3.0.tgz

to install the static version, run:
"inst bash-3.0-static"
or
'inst -c 147'

I can also specify more than one package at one time
"inst -c 147 256" would install 2 packages.

If only one package with specific name appears i.e
1515 joe-3.5.tgz
Then you could simply run
'inst joe'.


Maintained and updated by Kent Riboe - kent@alpcon.se


